1
00:00:07,970 --> 00:00:10,010
Why did you break other people’s things?

2
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,730
I wasn’t breaking things.

3
00:00:11,870 --> 00:00:14,510
The shop owner said
she wouldn’t mind if I did it.

4
00:00:14,870 --> 00:00:16,149
Are you screwing with me?

5
00:00:16,490 --> 00:00:18,170
Master is criticizing me again.

6
00:00:18,750 --> 00:00:20,880
Gen. Just call me Gen.

7
00:00:21,570 --> 00:00:22,560
Gen.

8
00:00:24,170 --> 00:00:25,180
Oh, sorry!

9
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:27,270
Kaew…

10
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:32,630
Next week, I’m meeting up with
the friends we joined the company with.

11
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,710
She’s been out of the picture for years.

12
00:00:34,790 --> 00:00:37,050
I wouldn’t have the guts to come if I were her.

13
00:00:40,550 --> 00:00:41,560
Sawasdee ka.

14
00:00:44,710 --> 00:00:46,650
Come on, follow me.

15
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:52,840
- What?
- Do we really have to go this far, honey?

16
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:53,740
Shh!

17
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:57,210
Today, we must find out
who Nong Gen’s girlfriend is,

18
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:58,450
where she’s from, and what she does!

19
00:00:58,480 --> 00:01:00,060
This is serious village business.

20
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:02,390
And we're the village's only hope.

21
00:01:03,820 --> 00:01:04,819
Go keep a lookout.

22
00:01:06,410 --> 00:01:07,930
- Ouch! What the hell?!
- Oh!

23
00:01:09,330 --> 00:01:11,110
Ahhh! A ghost!

24
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,710
Is it gone yet? Is it gone yet?
See if it's gone yet!

25
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:17,330
P’ Zoon, it’s Nong Ai.

26
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:18,340
Get up!

27
00:01:20,340 --> 00:01:21,620
Hi there, Nong Ai.

28
00:01:21,730 --> 00:01:23,270
What are you doing?

29
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:27,080
Gosh. Thought she was a Japanese
ghost with that long, flowing hair.

30
00:01:28,039 --> 00:01:30,250
Uh, beautiful—I mean, Nong Ai!

31
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:32,870
We weren't following you
or snooping around at all.

32
00:01:33,340 --> 00:01:36,039
Right? We really don’t want to
know anything about you at all.

33
00:01:38,430 --> 00:01:39,320
That’s enough!

34
00:01:39,979 --> 00:01:42,740
Nong Ai, we were just out for a stroll.

35
00:01:42,780 --> 00:01:46,940
A little nighttime date...
so romantic, don't you think?

36
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:49,470
- That’s right.
- Well, we'll be going now.

37
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:52,580
Have a nice date.

38
00:01:52,789 --> 00:01:54,720
Uh... thanks.

39
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,190
Go.

40
00:02:16,260 --> 00:02:17,470
Now, how do I do this?

41
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:31,730
Gen, who is this?

42
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:34,810
Uh...

43
00:02:34,829 --> 00:02:37,140
I’m Ai, Gen’s girlfriend.

44
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:41,170
Sorry I’m late.

45
00:02:54,530 --> 00:02:57,100
When we talked that day,
I thought you were single.

46
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:00,310
Because you...

47
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:32,820
Mind if I join you?

48
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:37,940
Not at all! Please, join us.

49
00:03:38,340 --> 00:03:40,120
Scoot over.
You can sit here.

50
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,050
Ai, no.

51
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:01,960
Thank you.

52
00:04:03,090 --> 00:04:04,010
Smells so good.

53
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:08,780
Um, if you don't mind me asking,
how did you two end up together?

54
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:10,160
Yeah. How?

55
00:04:11,170 --> 00:04:14,230
Exactly. How did you end
up with someone like Gen?

56
00:04:17,589 --> 00:04:21,240
Gen, I don't mean anything bad by it.

57
00:04:22,290 --> 00:04:23,410
I'm just curious.

58
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:30,970
The smell of cloves reminds me of the
massaman curry my mother used to make.

59
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:35,870
My mother always said that
if the heat is too high...

60
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,730
all you get is a sharp, smoky smell
instead of the flavor.

61
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:45,640
The curry needs to be simmered slowly
until it becomes rich and coats your tongue,

62
00:04:47,010 --> 00:04:48,740
not just a fleeting aroma.

63
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:52,720
Good things take time.

64
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,780
Some people don't even realize
they've let something good slip away.

65
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,140
Isn’t that right, Gen?

66
00:05:05,590 --> 00:05:07,260
That was sharper than any spice.

67
00:05:07,990 --> 00:05:08,910
Totally.

68
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:10,090
Was that a dig at me?

69
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:14,460
Uh, excuse us for a moment.

70
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:15,870
Ai.

71
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,020
We can talk here, Gen.

72
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:20,950
Ai!

73
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:25,440
Don't you want to know how I ended
up here and why I wasn't at home?

74
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,490
How do humans even make things like this?

75
00:05:40,130 --> 00:05:41,850
The beads are so tiny.

76
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:56,210
Please provide a simpler method suitable
for a less-than-one-month-old robot.

77
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:02,500
According to my analysis, 80% uneven,

78
00:06:02,530 --> 00:06:04,780
65% messy,

79
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,050
and 70% poorly arranged.

80
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:08,550
Conclusion...

81
00:06:10,530 --> 00:06:11,530
not pretty.

82
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,790
I need to finish it before Gen comes home.

83
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:41,770
It seems Gen is feeling shy.
We live together, you see.

84
00:08:42,850 --> 00:08:44,670
- Living together?
- Hold on.

85
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:48,700
Then do you mind if I ask how you two met?

86
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:51,230
Yeah, I want to know too.

87
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:54,700
It's been ages since we last met.
Give us an update. Come on.

88
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:57,830
We met through our work.

89
00:08:58,310 --> 00:08:59,050
Ai.

90
00:09:01,670 --> 00:09:05,000
I'm a researcher at a tech development company.

91
00:09:05,930 --> 00:09:10,150
The parent company is based in
the US, so I have to fly back and forth.

92
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:12,670
One of the times I came back,

93
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:16,590
I met Gen, who had joined
our company as a creative.

94
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:20,850
Can robots even lie?!
This is getting out of hand!

95
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,710
What’s the name of the company?

96
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,560
- It’s a secret!
- A secret?

97
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:29,260
It’s just a company name.

98
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:34,370
Or… could it be that everything
you've told us isn’t true?

99
00:09:34,890 --> 00:09:36,230
- Yeah.
- Right?

100
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:38,400
Come on, just tell us.

101
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,310
Kaew, stop it.

102
00:09:40,710 --> 00:09:42,570
It's okay if Gen doesn't want to tell us.

103
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,670
I don't have my business card with me today.

104
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:46,500
I only have my employee ID.

105
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,510
If you really want to know,
you can take a look.

106
00:09:51,540 --> 00:09:52,490
Pardon me.

107
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:55,570
“Lead Researcher…”

108
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:56,950
Wait a minute!

109
00:09:57,210 --> 00:10:00,120
This is a major global company!

110
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:02,610
Yeah, that’s right!
It’s very famous!

111
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,480
I really want to work there.

112
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:06,810
Then why keep it a secret?

113
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:08,030
Yeah.

114
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:10,930
Gen didn't want anyone to know where she worked.

115
00:10:13,130 --> 00:10:17,300
Gen has always told me that she doesn’t like
people judging her based on appearances.

116
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:20,650
And neither of us really cares
what the other does for a living.

117
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:24,330
We only care about who we truly are.

118
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:29,130
She makes me feel that way.

119
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:44,910
A message from the lab.
I need to go in and check on something.

120
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:47,150
Can I have my ID back, please?

121
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,020
Uh, yes, of course.

122
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:52,690
I'll be going now.

123
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:57,380
Wait. You can't go by yourself.
Let's head back together.

124
00:10:58,170 --> 00:10:59,290
You stay with your friends.

125
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:07,620
See you at home.

126
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:09,480
So lovey-dovey.

127
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:15,460
Wow, you quit a good job to go freelance

128
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:17,890
and ended up dating
a researcher at a major company.

129
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:19,160
I'm so happy for you.

130
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:20,530
Hey.

131
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:23,290
Gen.

132
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:26,560
I… I have to go.

133
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:34,920
This is awkward.

134
00:11:37,940 --> 00:11:39,440
Actually, I came here to return this.

135
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:42,080
I hope we never see each other again.

136
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:53,950
Ai! Wait!

137
00:12:01,170 --> 00:12:01,990
Sorry.

138
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:17,920
What was that just now?

139
00:12:19,650 --> 00:12:20,510
Was that Ai?

140
00:12:22,490 --> 00:12:23,490
The robot girl?

141
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:33,370
Didn't know she had this side to her.

142
00:12:51,490 --> 00:12:52,850
Hello, Khun Ploy.

143
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,660
Thank you for handling the urgent request.

144
00:12:55,990 --> 00:12:57,290
You’re very welcome.

145
00:12:57,640 --> 00:13:00,220
If you need anything else,
feel free to let me know anytime.

146
00:13:00,650 --> 00:13:01,790
I'll take care of it.

147
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:04,660
I'll transfer the remaining
amount to you shortly.

148
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:06,150
Thank you.

149
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:08,830
Uh... may I ask you a quick question?

150
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:12,210
The team member who
worked on your latest project

151
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:14,630
said she’d like to return
something she received from you.

152
00:13:14,890 --> 00:13:16,080
I’m not sure if—

153
00:13:16,110 --> 00:13:17,580
As we discussed before,

154
00:13:17,820 --> 00:13:21,140
I’m not able to disclose the address
or any company information.

155
00:13:21,660 --> 00:13:24,340
But I think she was quite
satisfied with what she got.

156
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,550
Pardon?

157
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:30,080
Anyway, I’ll contact you
within the next two or three days

158
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,730
and send over the information
for the next project.

159
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:34,910
I’ll be counting on you to take care of it.

160
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,260
Oh, of course.

161
00:13:37,460 --> 00:13:39,140
Thank you very much, Khun Irene.

162
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,620
I’ll be in touch.

163
00:14:04,970 --> 00:14:08,360
If I fail again, my mom’s gonna kill me.

164
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,780
Why can't I ever get this right?

165
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:16,010
Come on, calm down.

166
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:20,390
All these stupid rules and formulas.
Why do we even have to learn physics?

167
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,440
It's not like we're going
to use it when we grow up.

168
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,920
Try drawing it out first
and then apply the formula.

169
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,770
It might make it easier.

170
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:40,330
How do you mean, big sis?

171
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:41,910
Let me borrow that.

172
00:14:43,810 --> 00:14:49,340
First, you need to draw this line
to find the x-axis and y-axis.

173
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:52,650
That’s it.

174
00:14:55,230 --> 00:14:56,780
Physics isn't just about numbers.

175
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,080
It's a language for telling the story of motion.

176
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,680
Whoa.

177
00:15:02,490 --> 00:15:04,490
Why can't our teacher explain it like this?

178
00:15:04,930 --> 00:15:06,530
I finally understand it today.

179
00:15:06,810 --> 00:15:07,980
Are you a teacher, big sis?

180
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:12,800
No. I just usually spend
all day working with data

181
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,100
and with things that aren't human.

182
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,390
Wow, that’s so cool.

183
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:21,510
Big sis, you’re not only beautiful but kind too.

184
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:23,840
I'm not usually this kind, you know.

185
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:28,500
It's just that someone changed my perspective.

186
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:33,490
Helping people for a change feels
kind of strange, but in a good way.

187
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:40,320
Anyway, thank you so much for helping us out.

188
00:15:40,430 --> 00:15:43,680
If it weren't for you,
we probably wouldn’t have gotten it.

189
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:47,570
Exactly. We can't thank you enough.

190
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:50,390
Just do your best with your studies.

191
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,250
I have to go.

192
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:55,940
Class, show your respect.

193
00:15:56,850 --> 00:15:59,370
Thank you, teacher!

194
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:32,400
Hello, P’ Ploy.

195
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:35,850
Hey Gen, get ready. We’ll probably
get a new brief in a few days.

196
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:36,670
Okay.

197
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:39,220
What’s gotten into you today?
No complaining?

198
00:16:39,330 --> 00:16:40,330
Did something happen?

199
00:16:40,490 --> 00:16:41,340
Nope.

200
00:16:42,230 --> 00:16:44,610
Gen, be serious.
Are you keeping secrets now?

201
00:16:45,390 --> 00:16:48,910
Nothing. I’m just a little tight on money
lately, so I want to take on more work.

202
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:50,520
As if I’d buy that.

203
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:54,990
Anyway, I asked the client
about returning that item for you.

204
00:16:56,970 --> 00:16:57,820
And?

205
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:02,750
They said you can’t return it.

206
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:05,000
Oh.

207
00:17:06,710 --> 00:17:08,450
That’s it? What’s wrong with you?

208
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:12,099
You were making such a big deal about it,
and now you’re acting like it’s nothing?

209
00:17:14,050 --> 00:17:17,150
Well, they won't let me return it,
so what else am I supposed to do?

210
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:20,000
Why is everyone saying such weird things today?

211
00:17:25,369 --> 00:17:29,230
Hey P’ Ploy, have you ever
seen a system glitch out?

212
00:17:29,380 --> 00:17:31,450
It usually follows every command perfectly,

213
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:33,470
then all of a sudden it
starts thinking for itself.

214
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:36,720
Like in those doomsday movies
where AI takes over the world.

215
00:17:36,870 --> 00:17:39,710
What are you on about? Look at me.
I have a hundred different sides,

216
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:41,070
depending on who I’m with.

217
00:17:41,820 --> 00:17:43,510
Forget it. You’re no help at all.

218
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:46,190
What? Why?
You’d better spill it.

219
00:17:46,210 --> 00:17:48,900
You’ve been acting weird since earlier.
Are you in love?

220
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:51,670
Yeah, I’m just being weird.
I’m hanging up.

221
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:53,140
Don’t worry about the work.

222
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:56,310
Once I get the brief, I’ll get right on it.
You’ll have it in no time.

223
00:17:56,390 --> 00:17:57,550
- What?
- Bye.

224
00:17:57,570 --> 00:17:58,610
Gen, hold on—

225
00:18:18,780 --> 00:18:20,330
Welcome home.

226
00:18:20,570 --> 00:18:24,660
You came home 2 hours and
3 minutes later than your average today.

227
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:31,340
Says the one who went home first.

228
00:18:31,990 --> 00:18:34,290
Do you even realize what you've done? Huh?

229
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:39,360
I’m doing something that
I hope will make you smile.

230
00:18:39,580 --> 00:18:42,240
But I'd rather not tell you just yet.

231
00:18:43,090 --> 00:18:44,220
Is that okay?

232
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:45,710
Robots can lie?

233
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,870
Standard protocol prohibits lying.

234
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:50,220
The only permitted measures
are privacy protection

235
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:52,590
and generalized responses to avoid causing harm.

236
00:18:52,620 --> 00:18:56,700
What about food aromas?
Like the spices in massaman curry.

237
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:57,980
Can you smell all of those too?

238
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:03,250
I have micro-sensors in my simulated nasal
cavity that detect volatile compounds.

239
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:06,520
I can compare the patterns
with a database of spice aromas.

240
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:07,770
Would you like to see?

241
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:09,980
- I’ll open it up and show you.
- No, no, don’t!

242
00:19:27,150 --> 00:19:28,160
What are you doing?

243
00:19:36,260 --> 00:19:41,630
For example, I can detect the smell of alcohol
and your increasing heart rate right now.

244
00:19:43,020 --> 00:19:45,530
Are you feeling excited or anxious, Gen?

245
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:51,450
Hey, I told you to stop analyzing me.

246
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,450
I’m sleepy.

247
00:19:55,310 --> 00:19:56,310
I’m going to bed.

248
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:07,290
I have to finish it tonight.

249
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:17,000
Can humans really have feelings for a robot?

250
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:21,910
No. I’m probably just lonely.

251
00:20:24,340 --> 00:20:26,920
But why does my heart race like
it's about to explode every time?

252
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:30,390
Ugh! I don't know!

253
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:58,280
What are you doing?

254
00:21:00,430 --> 00:21:03,280
I want to sleep next to you.
Is that okay?

255
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:05,090
This is bad, Gen!

256
00:21:05,380 --> 00:21:07,130
Get a grip. Hold it together.

257
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:12,250
I’m sorry if I upset you. I’ll—

258
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:17,960
I didn’t say anything.

259
00:21:19,650 --> 00:21:22,490
But… can robots even sleep?

260
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:27,330
It’s not exactly actual sleep.
More like a sleep mode.

261
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:29,960
I deactivate unnecessary
systems to conserve energy

262
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:32,400
and lower my temperature so my
components don’t wear out too quickly.

263
00:21:33,010 --> 00:21:35,660
During sleep mode, I organize
the data collected throughout the day

264
00:21:35,690 --> 00:21:37,530
and delete the unnecessary parts.

265
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:40,740
Have you fallen asleep, Gen?

266
00:21:40,990 --> 00:21:43,020
Mmh... keep going.

267
00:21:46,530 --> 00:21:50,850
So, is it true that people sleep better
when they’re being held by someone?

268
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:54,170
Where do you get all this information from?

269
00:21:55,670 --> 00:21:57,910
I synthesize information
from multiple layers of data.

270
00:21:57,940 --> 00:22:01,470
I start by scanning human
sleep patterns in social contexts,

271
00:22:01,490 --> 00:22:04,810
then compare them with research on physical
touch and the autonomic nervous system.

272
00:22:04,830 --> 00:22:09,390
After that, I perform cross-validation
with anonymized behavioral data,

273
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:11,680
as well as self-reported experience records.

274
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:14,570
Ultimately, the probability indicates that

275
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,950
hugging may make it easier to fall
asleep for certain groups of people,

276
00:22:18,310 --> 00:22:22,570
especially when factors such as a sense
of safety and familiarity are involved.

277
00:22:23,670 --> 00:22:26,180
In summary, this isn’t based on personal belief.

278
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:28,450
It’s an inference drawn from multiple sources.

279
00:22:29,660 --> 00:22:31,270
Anything else you’d like to know, Gen?

280
00:22:39,110 --> 00:22:39,950
Gen?

281
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:57,610
Based on the fact that you fell
asleep more easily than usual,

282
00:22:58,830 --> 00:23:01,510
this hypothesis is likely correct.

283
00:23:33,380 --> 00:23:34,380
Thank you.

284
00:23:36,850 --> 00:23:39,700
Did you lock up the house properly last night?

285
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:45,590
I checked. The front door, windows,
and lights were all secured properly.

286
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:49,890
Except… you heart, which doesn’t
seem to be locked up properly.

287
00:23:50,420 --> 00:23:51,410
H-Hold on.

288
00:23:52,450 --> 00:23:55,150
Since when did robots get this cringey?

289
00:23:56,610 --> 00:24:00,340
Yesterday, I downloaded
additional romantic joke databases

290
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:03,240
because I noticed that you smile
when you hear things like this.

291
00:24:08,870 --> 00:24:09,870
You’re unbelievable.

292
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:12,260
Take that!

293
00:24:18,850 --> 00:24:19,850
What's this?

294
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:22,280
Something I wanted to give you.

295
00:24:23,530 --> 00:24:26,110
I want you to wear it and feel less sad.

296
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:39,380
I thought you said you didn't understand art.

297
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:44,430
I’m learning how to be human.

298
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:48,860
I want to understand
everything about you better,

299
00:24:48,890 --> 00:24:50,650
so I can stay by your side.

300
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:01,080
I apologize for analyzing you,

301
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:06,180
but your heart rate is currently
22% higher than normal.

302
00:25:07,510 --> 00:25:10,080
Are you feeling anxious or excited?

303
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,520
Probably the latter.

304
00:25:21,450 --> 00:25:26,740
~ Until the day I met you ~

305
00:25:27,260 --> 00:25:31,260
~ You came and broke down my walls ~

306
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:34,870
~ Now I know that good love looks just like you ~

307
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:37,770
~ I’m glad that we found each other ~

308
00:25:37,790 --> 00:25:41,970
~ Your love feels like a dream ~

309
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:45,290
~ Whatever tomorrow may bring ~

310
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,530
~ Whether it’s good or bad ~

311
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:46,640
Thank you.

312
00:25:47,550 --> 00:25:50,690
~ I believe everything...

313
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:53,520
Ai, what’s wrong?

314
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:57,510
The system temperature
is rising for no clear reason.

315
00:25:58,170 --> 00:26:01,490
I’ll activate soft mode because
my core is working too hard.

316
00:26:17,540 --> 00:26:18,540
It’s okay.

317
00:26:22,810 --> 00:26:24,370
My heart’s racing too.

318
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:38,150
~ Now I know that good love looks just like you ~

319
00:26:38,170 --> 00:26:41,040
~ I’m glad that we found each other ~

320
00:26:41,060 --> 00:26:45,270
~ Your love feels like a dream ~

321
00:26:45,290 --> 00:26:48,590
~ Whatever tomorrow may bring ~

322
00:26:48,610 --> 00:26:50,870
~ Whether it’s good or bad ~

323
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:55,340
~ I believe everything will be alright ~

324
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:59,120
~ Because I have you who understands me ~

325
00:27:22,410 --> 00:27:26,320
A382's response readings
are significantly above average.

326
00:27:28,150 --> 00:27:30,000
It's almost as if it's becoming more human.

327
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:35,530
That means A382 is learning
faster than we thought.

328
00:27:36,240 --> 00:27:37,810
From its environment...

329
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:40,820
and from Gen.

330
00:27:42,750 --> 00:27:45,800
Is it really a good idea to let
A382 get this close to a human?

331
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:49,290
Our objective is to collect the data
and bring the robot back.

332
00:27:50,910 --> 00:27:52,880
But if we bring A382 back now,

333
00:27:52,910 --> 00:27:57,950
we’ll never find out how closely
its heart can resemble a human's.

334
00:28:53,490 --> 00:28:58,170
And I decided to move forward
again... because of a certain someone.

335
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:31,360
You’re wearing the bracelet I made for you.

336
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,880
Well... it’s pretty.
It doesn’t make me itchy.

337
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:39,920
I’m so happy.

338
00:29:40,630 --> 00:29:43,290
What I did made you feel better, didn’t it?

339
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:47,730
Mm.

340
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:58,640
How many pieces are you going to work on today?

341
00:29:59,010 --> 00:30:03,660
Khun Ploy sent you two briefs this morning,
and Khun Petch sent you another one.

342
00:30:03,690 --> 00:30:07,300
And your mother sent a message
reminding you not to forget to call her,

343
00:30:07,450 --> 00:30:11,040
- ...along with three other messages—
- You’re just as nosy as the neighbors.

344
00:30:11,670 --> 00:30:13,090
I’m not nosy.

345
00:30:13,610 --> 00:30:17,830
I’m just trying to help you prioritize
your tasks so your work will be easier.

346
00:30:42,810 --> 00:30:45,570
I still don’t fully understand this feeling,

347
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:49,360
but I hope you don’t
have to feel this way often.

348
00:30:55,940 --> 00:31:02,300
Then… stay here with me
until I can get my head straight.

349
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:06,500
I’d be more than happy to.

350
00:31:41,210 --> 00:31:43,070
We’re here, Nong Joob.

351
00:31:43,450 --> 00:31:46,870
Just so you know,
I normally don’t work before noon.

352
00:31:47,420 --> 00:31:51,550
But since you’re P’ Gen’s little sister,
I’ll make an exception.

353
00:31:52,590 --> 00:31:56,430
Thank you, P’ Josh.
I feel extremely honored.

354
00:31:56,880 --> 00:31:58,440
Here, keep the change.

355
00:31:59,620 --> 00:32:05,280
Whoa, you’re cute and generous,
totally unlike your sister.

356
00:32:05,420 --> 00:32:07,510
If you ever need a ride, just let me know.

357
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:10,120
I’ll take you anywhere,
anytime, day or night.

358
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:13,310
I’ll get going.
Bye, Nong Joob.

359
00:32:13,340 --> 00:32:14,690
- Bye.
- Just give me a call.

360
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:22,880
Look! A new character has appeared.

361
00:32:35,130 --> 00:32:39,030
My apologies. This residence is
temporarily off-limits to outsiders.

362
00:32:39,220 --> 00:32:43,020
If your name isn’t registered in the database
or you don’t know anyone in this house,

363
00:32:43,060 --> 00:32:46,660
please maintain a safe distance... of 2 meters.

364
00:32:48,390 --> 00:32:50,800
What about you?
Aren't you an outsider?

365
00:32:50,910 --> 00:32:53,030
Are you actually registered
in this house’s database?

366
00:32:54,660 --> 00:32:56,750
You are not on the visitor list.

367
00:32:56,770 --> 00:32:57,870
What’s wrong with you?!

368
00:33:01,020 --> 00:33:03,240
P’ Gen! P’ Gen!

369
00:33:03,260 --> 00:33:05,810
Some stranger won’t let me into the house!

370
00:33:08,930 --> 00:33:10,150
I’m going in! Oh!

371
00:33:10,170 --> 00:33:12,700
- You can’t.
- Ugh! Who are you?!

372
00:33:12,940 --> 00:33:13,730
Let go!

373
00:33:14,830 --> 00:33:17,320
Here we go, honey. Should
we step in and break it up?

374
00:33:17,340 --> 00:33:19,200
Not yet.
Hold this for me.

375
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:22,300
Breaking news! The epic showdown:
The Wife’s Sister vs. The Sister-in-Law.

376
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:24,810
Who will survive and
who will fall? Stay tuned!

377
00:33:25,360 --> 00:33:28,220
Wife’s sister? Sister-in-law?
Is that even a thing, darling?

378
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:29,900
Usually, it's mother-in-law
and daughter-in-law drama.

379
00:33:32,270 --> 00:33:34,410
Just watch!
They’re about to have a catfight.

380
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:36,750
Let go! I said let go!

381
00:33:36,770 --> 00:33:37,630
Stop!!!

382
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:44,660
P’ Gen! Who is this woman?!
She won't let me into the house!

383
00:33:45,030 --> 00:33:47,690
Look! She’s even trying to assault me!

384
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:52,040
- Your name isn’t on the visitor list—
- Whoa, whoa, wait!

385
00:33:52,770 --> 00:33:54,750
This is Joob, my little sister.

386
00:33:55,140 --> 00:33:56,510
And this is Ai. She’s…

387
00:33:58,470 --> 00:33:59,850
my roommate.

388
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:05,880
Information updated.
Joob, Gen’s younger sister.

389
00:34:09,460 --> 00:34:11,659
I’m sorry. I didn’t know.

390
00:34:12,389 --> 00:34:13,900
Apology not accepted.

391
00:34:15,139 --> 00:34:17,380
Who are you ? Where are you from?
How do you know P’ Gen?

392
00:34:17,409 --> 00:34:19,380
Why are you her roommate?
What’s your job?

393
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:21,350
How long will you be staying here?
Do you pay rent?

394
00:34:21,380 --> 00:34:22,900
- Do you have siblings? Are you single?
- Joob.

395
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,489
Wait! Do you have crush on P’ Gen?
Or—

396
00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:26,920
Joob, Joob, calm down!
Let’s talk inside.

397
00:34:27,670 --> 00:34:28,389
Come on.

398
00:34:28,420 --> 00:34:30,020
Which question should I start with?

399
00:34:30,830 --> 00:34:32,670
All of them! Answer me!

400
00:34:32,690 --> 00:34:34,400
- Then, first question—
- Stop!

401
00:34:34,980 --> 00:34:37,280
Both of you, get inside!

402
00:34:38,790 --> 00:34:40,750
There are walking CCTV cameras around here.

403
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:43,060
Their eyes and ears are faster than 5G Wi-Fi.

404
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:44,659
Come on.

405
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:55,770
Did she just call us out, honey?

406
00:34:56,530 --> 00:34:58,270
If you want to take offense, that’s on you.

407
00:34:59,290 --> 00:35:00,660
Hey! Wait for me!

408
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:20,390
Are you screwing with me? Hm?

409
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:26,950
You!

410
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:30,410
This is Ai, my roommate.

411
00:35:30,450 --> 00:35:32,520
She’s helping me with work
and staying here for a while.

412
00:35:32,540 --> 00:35:33,590
That’s it. End of story.

413
00:35:34,810 --> 00:35:36,350
- Then—
- And what are you doing here?

414
00:35:36,500 --> 00:35:38,160
Did you miss me, or need help with work?

415
00:35:40,020 --> 00:35:42,110
Of course, I missed you!

416
00:35:42,580 --> 00:35:44,240
It’s been so long.

417
00:35:44,270 --> 00:35:46,380
I’ve been away shooting travel vlogs for months.

418
00:35:46,750 --> 00:35:49,970
And I came to see you
first thing when I got back.

419
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:53,800
I don’t think I could sleep
if I didn’t get to see you.

420
00:35:55,460 --> 00:35:56,460
Is that all?

421
00:35:57,380 --> 00:35:58,820
And…

422
00:35:59,770 --> 00:36:03,040
I happen to have a new
camera that I need to review,

423
00:36:03,580 --> 00:36:04,750
so I wanted you to—

424
00:36:04,770 --> 00:36:06,190
I frickin’ knew it.

425
00:36:07,220 --> 00:36:11,500
Oh come on, P’ Gen!
Please, please, please.

426
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:13,680
Please help me out.
Please, please, please.

427
00:36:13,710 --> 00:36:15,400
Please, P’ Gen, my beautiful sister.

428
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:20,750
Ever since I was born, no one has ever shot
my content as well as you. You know that?

429
00:36:21,430 --> 00:36:23,160
Pretty please…

430
00:36:23,550 --> 00:36:24,550
I know.

431
00:36:24,750 --> 00:36:26,590
But I need to finish my work first, okay?

432
00:36:27,870 --> 00:36:30,500
Yay! You’re the best sister in the world!

433
00:36:34,140 --> 00:36:35,150
Don’t get handsy.

434
00:36:36,710 --> 00:36:38,820
In the meantime, ask Ai
for help if you need anything.

435
00:36:39,100 --> 00:36:40,110
I have to work.

436
00:36:40,570 --> 00:36:43,520
And no fighting.

437
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:46,710
Okay.

438
00:37:03,660 --> 00:37:05,070
What can I help you with?

439
00:37:06,330 --> 00:37:10,760
If necessary, I can set the white
balance, test the rolling shutter,

440
00:37:10,780 --> 00:37:13,150
apply basic LUTs, and operate the gimbal.

441
00:37:15,930 --> 00:37:19,280
Who on earth are you?
You know more about cameras than I do.

442
00:37:24,250 --> 00:37:28,040
Ugh! Why do I have so much stuff?!

443
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,840
I still need to set up the camera
and take it out for a test shoot.

444
00:37:33,110 --> 00:37:34,750
Argh! I’m going crazy!

445
00:37:37,130 --> 00:37:39,740
Would you like me to sort
everything into categories?

446
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:47,390
For example: camera gear,
toys, clothes, makeup...

447
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:49,040
and trash.

448
00:37:52,070 --> 00:37:54,520
If you sort all my stuff and
I can still find them afterward,

449
00:37:54,540 --> 00:37:56,590
I'll give you a perfect ten.

450
00:37:57,880 --> 00:38:00,420
Don't you remember what your
room was like when we were kids?

451
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:01,660
It was even messier than this.

452
00:38:01,970 --> 00:38:03,410
Come on, P’ Gen.

453
00:38:03,430 --> 00:38:06,500
Who could ever be as perfectly neat as you?

454
00:38:06,910 --> 00:38:09,870
You were Mom's golden child.
I always got scolded.

455
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:22,520
P’ Gen...

456
00:38:24,110 --> 00:38:25,280
I'm sorry.

457
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:27,780
I didn't mean it.

458
00:38:29,690 --> 00:38:30,700
I know that.

459
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:35,000
I’m going to submit my work.
Play nice, you two.

460
00:38:46,130 --> 00:38:47,570
You shouldn’t have said it, Ai Joob.

461
00:38:55,140 --> 00:38:56,090
Hey!

462
00:38:58,120 --> 00:38:59,120
All done.

463
00:39:02,010 --> 00:39:02,970
No way...

464
00:39:04,500 --> 00:39:05,500
This is impossible.

465
00:39:08,650 --> 00:39:09,660
Shall we begin?

466
00:39:11,290 --> 00:39:13,660
One Day Vlog with Me, everyone!

467
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:15,950
What happened?
Why on earth won't it focus?

468
00:39:15,970 --> 00:39:17,110
Let me help you.

469
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:18,840
Are you sure?

470
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:20,760
Alright, give it a try.

471
00:39:21,630 --> 00:39:23,720
One Day Vlog with Me, everyone!

472
00:39:23,740 --> 00:39:28,340
Today, I’m taking you to see the community
garden where P’ Gen, my sister, lives.

473
00:39:28,370 --> 00:39:32,660
Let’s go check out the garden. Come on!

474
00:39:32,690 --> 00:39:33,780
Come on, let me see.

475
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:37,910
How are your hands so steady?

476
00:39:38,530 --> 00:39:39,540
Can we try again?

477
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:42,740
One Day Vlog with Me, everyone!

478
00:39:42,770 --> 00:39:46,760
Today, I’m taking you to see the
community garden where P’ Gen lives.

479
00:39:46,780 --> 00:39:50,170
Everyone, come look!
Here it is, P’ Gen’s neighborhood garden!

480
00:39:50,560 --> 00:39:53,120
What do you think?
It’s really spacious, isn’t it?

481
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:54,040
Stop!

482
00:39:54,650 --> 00:39:55,560
Let me take a look.

483
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,010
Huh?

484
00:40:00,910 --> 00:40:02,200
How are your hands so steady?

485
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:04,890
It’s like you have gimbal arms or something.

486
00:40:11,100 --> 00:40:12,720
Let me see the photos.

487
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:15,740
I look amazing!

488
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:18,410
How did you even pull this off?!

489
00:40:24,370 --> 00:40:25,880
Wait, what was that?

490
00:40:26,240 --> 00:40:30,960
I adjusted the ISO and increased the
shutter speed to capture your poses quickly.

491
00:40:31,970 --> 00:40:35,050
Not that. Your ear... it...

492
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:38,440
I must’ve imagined it.

493
00:40:39,460 --> 00:40:42,270
This is a new-gen wireless mic.
It comes with a magnetic mount.

494
00:40:42,290 --> 00:40:44,080
Super convenient.

495
00:40:44,110 --> 00:40:45,950
You just attach it like this.

496
00:40:47,430 --> 00:40:48,370
Hey!

497
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:52,920
Something’s not right.

498
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:56,220
P’ Gen! P’ Gen...

499
00:40:57,570 --> 00:41:01,190
Just attach the magnets to the
clothes like this, and it’s ready to use.

500
00:41:02,740 --> 00:41:05,070
P’ Gen… Just now…

501
00:41:05,670 --> 00:41:08,390
- Just now, it…
- It’s so hot today!

502
00:41:08,830 --> 00:41:11,280
Hey, Joob!
Your foundation’s melted off.

503
00:41:11,310 --> 00:41:13,160
Is the footage you shot even usable?

504
00:41:13,180 --> 00:41:15,620
What?! Really?! Mirror!

505
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:18,030
I’ll go check the mirror first!

506
00:41:25,290 --> 00:41:26,350
That was close.

507
00:41:31,470 --> 00:41:33,230
Could you teach me how to take photos, Gen?

508
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:35,740
What do you mean?

509
00:41:36,420 --> 00:41:37,640
And what was that just now?

510
00:41:37,670 --> 00:41:40,080
I thought you weren’t supposed
to tell anyone you’re a robot.

511
00:41:40,700 --> 00:41:42,260
I didn’t tell anyone.

512
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:45,410
And I want to capture memories
the way humans do, by taking photos.

513
00:41:46,860 --> 00:41:49,510
But didn’t you just take photos for Joob earlier?

514
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:51,550
She wouldn’t stop saying
how beautiful they were.

515
00:41:51,690 --> 00:41:53,890
I used the automatic photography system.

516
00:41:54,070 --> 00:41:55,920
I want to learn the way humans take photos.

517
00:41:56,340 --> 00:42:00,230
Taking photos manually like this is
like choosing your own memories, isn’t it?

518
00:42:01,500 --> 00:42:04,070
I... suppose so.

519
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:06,960
Then, could I use your phone, Gen?

520
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:11,950
...Please? Please, please, please?

521
00:42:12,210 --> 00:42:14,540
- Please, please, please?
- My phone’s inside!

522
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:17,140
I’ll go get it.

523
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:21,920
You’re the best, Gen.

524
00:42:35,340 --> 00:42:37,030
Who taught her that?

525
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:51,600
See these lines?
It's called the rule of thirds.

526
00:42:51,830 --> 00:42:55,580
When you're taking a photo, try placing
your subject where the grid lines intersect.

527
00:42:55,710 --> 00:42:57,320
It makes the composition look nicer.

528
00:42:57,820 --> 00:42:58,830
Give it a try.

529
00:43:09,130 --> 00:43:10,940
If the subject is your face...

530
00:43:21,150 --> 00:43:22,210
Let me see.

531
00:43:22,970 --> 00:43:23,840
Ai.

532
00:43:23,860 --> 00:43:25,370
I'd like to try one more time.

533
00:43:25,400 --> 00:43:26,400
Give it to me.

534
00:43:27,780 --> 00:43:28,540
Gimme that.

535
00:43:36,900 --> 00:43:38,170
You’re laughing, Gen.

536
00:43:39,150 --> 00:43:40,730
Is this considered bullying?

537
00:43:42,300 --> 00:43:43,670
Just look at what you took!

538
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:45,900
You can barely even tell who this is.

539
00:43:48,510 --> 00:43:51,210
But you said to put the subject
at the intersection points.

540
00:43:52,060 --> 00:43:55,380
I just felt that everything
about you was a focal point.

541
00:43:58,180 --> 00:44:01,630
Your eyes, your nose, your mouth.

542
00:44:07,830 --> 00:44:10,040
You might as well just say I'm beautiful.

543
00:44:11,460 --> 00:44:12,270
Yes.

544
00:44:14,610 --> 00:44:15,610
You’re beautiful.

545
00:44:24,010 --> 00:44:26,530
Jeez, you're talking nonsense now.

546
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:29,470
Then, may I try again?

547
00:44:31,390 --> 00:44:33,140
Mm. Here.

548
00:44:43,450 --> 00:44:45,930
That's enough.
I'll show you how it’s done.

549
00:44:46,290 --> 00:44:48,590
Now this is how you do it.

550
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:50,910
There's a selfie mode too.

551
00:44:52,110 --> 00:44:53,580
Okay, look right here.

552
00:44:54,410 --> 00:44:56,370
Smile! One, two, three!

553
00:44:57,010 --> 00:44:58,600
Cheese!

554
00:45:00,900 --> 00:45:02,670
Do it properly. Like this.

555
00:45:18,270 --> 00:45:20,320
How long are you planning
to stay with me this time?

556
00:45:20,950 --> 00:45:23,720
Hmm... probably a couple of days.

557
00:45:24,530 --> 00:45:27,180
I’m flying to Japan
for another road trip after this,

558
00:45:27,790 --> 00:45:29,510
so I won’t be mooching off you for long.

559
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:36,920
Besides, I just wanted to check
if my big sister is doing okay.

560
00:45:36,950 --> 00:45:38,320
I'm fine.

561
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:43,340
From what I've seen,
you really are doing fine.

562
00:45:43,790 --> 00:45:45,240
Too fine, actually.

563
00:45:46,020 --> 00:45:50,880
Now that you have your own personal
assistant, I’m no longer your favorite.

564
00:45:51,630 --> 00:45:53,060
What are you talking about?

565
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,620
But I’m happy, you know.

566
00:46:03,080 --> 00:46:04,390
Ever since I was born,

567
00:46:05,380 --> 00:46:07,440
I could probably count on one hand

568
00:46:08,120 --> 00:46:12,600
the number of times I’ve seen
you smile this big or laugh this freely.

569
00:46:20,770 --> 00:46:23,280
By the way, have you talked to Mom lately?

570
00:46:24,590 --> 00:46:31,740
She’s always asking me how you’re doing,
how far you’ve gotten with your promotions.

571
00:46:33,180 --> 00:46:36,370
She also said she wants you to move back home.

572
00:46:43,330 --> 00:46:44,460
It’s not easy...

573
00:46:45,340 --> 00:46:48,070
being yourself in front of someone
who wants to see you succeed,

574
00:46:48,990 --> 00:46:50,960
but their idea of success
is different from yours.

575
00:46:55,360 --> 00:46:56,880
So, are you being yourself now?

576
00:46:57,370 --> 00:46:58,370
Absolutely.

577
00:47:00,670 --> 00:47:03,820
Especially when you’re around Ai, right?

578
00:47:04,450 --> 00:47:06,750
Ai Joob! What are you talking about?

579
00:47:06,770 --> 00:47:09,190
- Delete them. Delete all of them.
- I saw it! I saw it!

580
00:47:10,240 --> 00:47:11,640
- Sis.
- What?

581
00:47:12,190 --> 00:47:13,260
I’m serious.

582
00:47:14,410 --> 00:47:16,730
I think you should tell Mom you quit your job.

583
00:47:22,730 --> 00:47:24,820
You’ve already lost love once.

584
00:47:27,690 --> 00:47:31,710
Are you… going to let it happen again?

585
00:47:47,830 --> 00:47:49,190
I’d better get back to work.

586
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:51,620
Take your time choosing.

587
00:47:55,710 --> 00:47:56,500
Alright?

588
00:48:35,630 --> 00:48:42,850
Back then, whenever I was stressed,
I’d come over to P’ Gen’s place

589
00:48:44,280 --> 00:48:48,510
and wonder why she never seemed relaxed.

590
00:48:51,040 --> 00:48:56,560
Since I moved in with Gen,
her stress levels, mood, and sleep

591
00:48:56,590 --> 00:49:02,440
have shown improvements of
8%, 17%, and 24%, respectively.

592
00:49:03,720 --> 00:49:08,790
And over the past few days, her
happiness level has increased by 31%.

593
00:49:09,870 --> 00:49:11,060
Based on my analysis,

594
00:49:12,280 --> 00:49:15,030
I’d say Gen seems more relaxed.

595
00:49:17,910 --> 00:49:20,020
Do you have to calculate
everything down to a number?

596
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:22,730
How are you even measuring that? Hm?

597
00:49:25,090 --> 00:49:26,260
I can’t tell you.

598
00:49:28,150 --> 00:49:29,110
Never mind.

599
00:49:30,670 --> 00:49:32,390
You’re pretty weird, you know.

600
00:49:34,630 --> 00:49:37,120
Weird… but in a good way, right?

601
00:49:40,060 --> 00:49:44,020
Anyone who can make P’ Gen smile
is good in my book.

602
00:49:50,940 --> 00:49:51,940
You know...

603
00:49:53,650 --> 00:49:57,680
I never thought that a person’s
love and good intentions

604
00:49:58,000 --> 00:50:00,300
could end up hurting another person.

605
00:50:01,610 --> 00:50:03,340
And I don’t understand at all

606
00:50:04,220 --> 00:50:08,030
how someone can carry
another person’s feelings, dreams,

607
00:50:08,460 --> 00:50:11,910
and expectations on their
shoulders for ten, twenty years.

608
00:50:14,590 --> 00:50:17,580
If it were me, I’d probably break.

609
00:50:20,960 --> 00:50:24,640
And the worst part is, those two
people are the ones I love most.

610
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:27,740
I don’t understand.

611
00:50:29,920 --> 00:50:32,400
You don't have to understand right now.

612
00:50:33,720 --> 00:50:39,670
Just stay by P’ Gen’s side and keep
making her smile like this for a long time.

613
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:44,890
I can take care of Gen for the rest of her life.

614
00:50:50,340 --> 00:50:51,230
You promised.

615
00:50:52,510 --> 00:50:53,730
So let’s become friends.

616
00:50:57,660 --> 00:50:59,880
Okay. Joob, my friend.

617
00:51:06,070 --> 00:51:07,910
Yeah, Ai, my friend.

618
00:51:12,450 --> 00:51:13,270
Like this.

619
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:17,720
That’s enough.

620
00:51:20,810 --> 00:51:21,810
What were you watching?

621
00:51:28,240 --> 00:51:29,030
What?

622
00:51:30,670 --> 00:51:33,390
Look at you, all whiny.
What’s wrong?

623
00:51:33,730 --> 00:51:36,520
I don't want to leave yet!

624
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:38,160
I’ve changed my mind.

625
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:40,240
I'll stay and mooch off you forever.

626
00:51:40,260 --> 00:51:42,270
You mean it?
Then I’ll put your suitcase back.

627
00:51:42,290 --> 00:51:43,300
Hey!

628
00:51:43,850 --> 00:51:46,990
Come on, P’ Gen.
My clients are going to kill me.

629
00:51:48,110 --> 00:51:51,030
Then work hard and don’t cause any trouble.

630
00:51:51,400 --> 00:51:53,250
And make sure to rest
plenty when you're tired.

631
00:51:54,300 --> 00:51:55,410
Got it, Mom.

632
00:51:55,610 --> 00:51:58,770
Look who's talking.
You should be telling yourself that.

633
00:51:58,970 --> 00:52:01,690
Take a break sometimes.
I worry about you, you know.

634
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:02,850
Mm.

635
00:52:03,180 --> 00:52:04,900
I’m leaving my sister in your care.

636
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:07,200
Gladly.

637
00:52:11,780 --> 00:52:12,700
You rascal.

638
00:52:13,960 --> 00:52:14,920
Your ride’s here.

639
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:18,700
Well, well, well!

640
00:52:19,010 --> 00:52:21,640
You’re actually pretty sweet
when you’re with your sister, P’ Gen.

641
00:52:21,870 --> 00:52:24,920
But with me? You look like a killer.

642
00:52:24,950 --> 00:52:26,200
- You got a problem?
- Stop, stop, stop!

643
00:52:26,220 --> 00:52:27,980
You’re going to set a bad example for her.

644
00:52:30,130 --> 00:52:31,570
Drive safe, Ai Josh.

645
00:52:31,590 --> 00:52:34,510
If my sister gets so much
as a scratch, you’re dead.

646
00:52:34,720 --> 00:52:36,180
Roger that, boss.

647
00:52:36,900 --> 00:52:40,420
I’ll drive nice and smooth.
Not a single fly will touch her.

648
00:52:40,730 --> 00:52:43,310
She’ll get there safe and sound, I promise.

649
00:52:43,340 --> 00:52:44,390
Just drive safe.

650
00:52:44,410 --> 00:52:46,060
Joob, let me know when you get there.

651
00:52:46,540 --> 00:52:47,830
Hey! Ai Josh!

652
00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:50,040
Wait! Joob, hold on tight!

653
00:52:50,070 --> 00:52:51,230
Wait! Joob, hang on tight!

654
00:52:59,270 --> 00:53:02,010
Now it’s just the two of us.

655
00:53:03,100 --> 00:53:04,720
- Do you feel lonely, Gen?
- Nope.

656
00:53:05,900 --> 00:53:07,680
Just having the two of us is nice too.

657
00:53:09,420 --> 00:53:10,690
What do you mean?

658
00:53:12,290 --> 00:53:16,130
Why don’t you… figure it out yourself?

659
00:53:17,860 --> 00:53:18,860
I’m heading inside.

660
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:20,650
What do you mean, Gen?

661
00:53:21,270 --> 00:53:23,900
Can you explain it to me?
I don’t understand.

662
00:53:36,600 --> 00:53:37,900
Hahahahaha.

663
00:53:40,060 --> 00:53:41,150
What are you laughing at?

664
00:53:43,300 --> 00:53:44,920
I laughed because you laughed.

665
00:53:45,290 --> 00:53:46,410
Hahahahaha.

666
00:53:46,970 --> 00:53:48,890
Laughing is what you’re supposed to do, right?

667
00:53:50,220 --> 00:53:53,250
Yeah, if it’s actually funny.

668
00:53:55,940 --> 00:53:58,700
Do you actually find it funny?
Do you even get the jokes?

669
00:54:01,390 --> 00:54:02,430
Maybe not yet.

670
00:54:06,660 --> 00:54:10,870
Look. If it’s not funny, you don't
have to force yourself to laugh.

671
00:54:11,510 --> 00:54:13,500
I just want to feel it with you, Gen.

672
00:54:31,050 --> 00:54:32,470
Do you want to hold hands?

673
00:54:34,300 --> 00:54:37,020
Hmmmm...

674
00:54:40,890 --> 00:54:42,910
Oh shit, a sex scene.

675
00:54:43,230 --> 00:54:44,770
What do I do, what do I do?!

676
00:54:46,520 --> 00:54:47,410
No!

677
00:54:48,110 --> 00:54:49,110
This isn’t for kids.

678
00:54:49,660 --> 00:54:50,660
Why?

679
00:54:51,200 --> 00:54:55,350
And why is that person touching the other’s leg?

680
00:54:55,370 --> 00:54:58,610
They just want something.
You’ll understand when you’re older.

681
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:01,010
Where’s the remote?

682
00:55:19,770 --> 00:55:22,190
Keep it together, Gen.
Keep it together.

683
00:55:35,170 --> 00:55:36,530
Breathe in.

684
00:55:37,680 --> 00:55:39,080
Breathe out.

685
00:55:39,400 --> 00:55:41,880
This is a robot. A robot!

686
00:55:42,210 --> 00:55:43,640
What is she doing?!

687
00:55:44,460 --> 00:55:46,940
What if I want something too?

688
00:55:55,300 --> 00:55:56,890
I can't take this anymore!!!

689
00:55:59,500 --> 00:56:00,510
What do you want?

690
00:56:03,840 --> 00:56:04,840
I...

691
00:56:09,560 --> 00:56:11,870
want to visit the exhibition
at the gallery again.

692
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:14,490
Huh?!

693
00:56:14,510 --> 00:56:17,860
I want to take your photo there.
Can you take me there?

694
00:56:19,260 --> 00:56:20,870
Are you being serious?

695
00:56:22,320 --> 00:56:23,620
Can we go tomorrow?

696
00:56:34,020 --> 00:56:34,880
Mm.

697
00:56:35,700 --> 00:56:39,000
I’m sleepy.
Make sure to turn off the TV.

698
00:56:43,100 --> 00:56:44,510
See you at 9 tomorrow.

699
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:55,220
Aren’t you coming to check the graphs
today? A382’s data is spiking like crazy.

700
00:56:55,500 --> 00:56:57,220
I’ll go over everything this evening.

701
00:57:09,400 --> 00:57:11,290
I want some time to myself today.

702
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:55,640
The concept of this exhibition
is to turn data into visual art.

703
00:57:56,340 --> 00:58:01,390
It’s interesting that they chose
light, color, and sound over numbers.

704
00:58:02,950 --> 00:58:05,290
You talk like you’ve been
in a lab like this before.

705
00:58:06,830 --> 00:58:09,180
I’m just familiar with similar graphs.

706
00:58:19,030 --> 00:58:19,970
Hey!

707
00:58:21,480 --> 00:58:22,480
I’m sorry.

708
00:58:23,510 --> 00:58:24,510
I’m sorry.

709
00:58:24,540 --> 00:58:26,020
Watch where you're going.

710
00:58:37,320 --> 00:58:41,140
I’ll hold your hand so you
don’t bump into anyone again.

711
00:58:57,540 --> 00:59:01,860
Ai, are you almost done?
My face is cramping from smiling.

712
00:59:03,170 --> 00:59:05,620
Almost done.
Just a little longer.

713
00:59:15,320 --> 00:59:17,060
Ai? What's wrong?

714
00:59:55,990 --> 00:59:57,580
What are you doing?

715
00:59:58,520 --> 01:00:00,210
You’re way too adorable.

716
01:00:12,330 --> 01:00:15,340
You idiot! Do you even
realize what you filmed?

717
01:00:23,820 --> 01:00:26,820
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.

718
01:00:27,290 --> 01:00:28,380
Silly girl.

719
01:00:32,060 --> 01:00:33,450
Hey! Wait!

720
01:00:34,740 --> 01:00:35,750
Who are you?

721
01:00:37,470 --> 01:00:40,790
Is it possible for two people
to look this much alike?

722
01:00:40,980 --> 01:00:43,150
Or is she another robot?

723
01:00:43,180 --> 01:00:46,420
No. The way she talks feels too human.

724
01:00:46,540 --> 01:00:50,920
A382 is starting to develop boundaries
and recognize its own space.

725
01:00:52,230 --> 01:00:54,980
Gen, is there something you want to tell me?

726
01:00:56,820 --> 01:00:59,330
Why did you hide this from me?

727
01:00:59,350 --> 01:01:01,030
- You don’t understand, Mom.
- You're right.

728
01:01:01,050 --> 01:01:03,030
I don’t know my own daughter at all.

729
01:01:04,780 --> 01:01:06,300
I need to talk to you.

